en_823498_0	The Finance Ministry has announced that liquor licenses had not been issued to any member of the present Parliament.
en_823498_1	While there are 4,910 liquor bars with all-purpose licenses in Sri Lanka, 1,100 among them are retail outlets.
en_823498_2	The Finance Ministry pointed out that there are 1,567 hotel liquor licenses and 554 restaurant licenses.
en_823498_3	The Ministry stated that any person desiring to obtain a liquor serving license could obtain a permit under the rules and regulations stipulated by the Excise Department.
en_823498_4	If obtaining such a license, one should not had been found guilty of any offence within the last five years and should also be a taxpayer.
en_823498_5	The Ministry of Finance stated that according to the type of liquor bars, they should be located within a reasonable distance from places of worship and schools.
en_823498_6	The Ministry of Finance mentioned that the list of liquor licenses issued has been published on the Excise Departmentâ€™s website for public reference.
